RACE.RACE_TEXT: PINE MTN-CALLOWAY GARDEN RACE 1 3 1/2M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 25000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. 160 lbs. Winners of a Steeplethon, 5 lbs. extra.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COURT RULER (IRE) led the field every step of the way, drawing off in the stretch. STORM TEAM settled just off the leader for the opening two laps and could not go with that rival through the final half mile but kept on in the lane. MERCOEUR (FR) raced off the pace through the early going, offered a bid approaching mile two and flattened out from there. RAKHAA (GB) trailed the field the first time around, pulled up midway through the second lap and was vanned off after walking onto the van.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Collie Jennings Mullin S. PINE MTN-CALLOWAY GARDEN RACE 2 2 3/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 35000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 120 OR LOWER. he highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including ap prentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANIMAL KINGSTON raced off the pace through the opening mile and a half, launched a bid coming into the stretch and dueled gamely to the wire to just get the win. FOR THE PARISH (IRE) chased the leader through the first lap, challenged on the outside nearing the second mile pole and battled gamely the length of the stretch to narrowly miss. GO POKE THE BEAR led the way through the opening mile, opened up on his competition the second time around, and was caught in upper stretch but finished well, keeping on the wire. PRESENCE OF MIND (IRE) chased the leader through the first lap, fell coming over fence five, was caught and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PINE MTN-CALLOWAY GARDEN RACE 3 2 3/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 142 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 150 lbs.; Older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOXY WALK (IRE) chased the leader through the first mile, launched a bid headed into lap two, and drew off in the stretch, much the best. MACHEEDA (IRE) raced off the pace on the outside around the first two laps and was no match for the winner in the lane, chasing that rival home. RIPTIDE ROCK stumbled coming over jump two, recovered to race off the pace through the next mile and a half and passed tiring horses in the stretch. MCSTEAMY led the way through the early going, opened up on the field the second time by and tired through the final half mile.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AFLAC Supreme Hurdle S. PINE MTN-CALLOWAY GARDEN RACE 4 2 3/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 75000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES For Four Year Olds and Upward which have not won over hurdles prior to September 1, 2022 or which have never won three races, other than three-year-old.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COOL JET (IRE) chased the leader off the pace through the opening lap, began a bid approaching mile two, dueled in the lane and edged clear late. THE HERO NEXT DOOR (IRE) led the way through the first mile, opened up on his rivals headed into the second lap, was challenged coming into the stretch, dueled and was outfinished late, the best of the rest. FAST VISION (FR) trailed the field through the opening two miles and was no match for the top two but kept on to the finish. CALICO (FR) chased the leaders the first time around, began to tire headed into the second lap and was eased through the final half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Calico (FR)
ENTRY.OWNER: Del Rio Racing LLC and Goldman Racing Syndicate

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PINE MTN-CALLOWAY GARDEN RACE 5 2 3/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 144 lbs.; Four Year Olds, 152 lbs.; Older, 156 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, For Each $2,500 To $20,000 4 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AGITARE (IRE) dueled on the inside through the opening two miles, alternating the lead with I AM FORTUNATA before shaking clear of that rival in the stretch. I AM FORTUNATA (IRE) traded the lead with AGITARE while racing outside through laps one and two, could not go with that rival late and chased him, the best of the rest. KARL CARES raced off the pace early, dropped back to trail the field coming around the second time and was outkicked in the lane. D'ARPINO B C raced off the pace through the opening mile, continued at the back of the pack from there and finished evenly.

ENTRY.NAME: Agitare (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Willis Molly Willis Paul CFC Stables Kelly Danny Kelly Sheila and L5 Racing
